                                                Careful monitoring of diuresis and renal function is recommended in
                                                patients with the
                                                following risk factors: (HYPERKALEMIA)
                                            </p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Elderly</li>
                                                <li>Concomitant treatments such as ACE inhibitors, angiotensin-II
                                                    antagonists, sartans,
                                                    diuretics </li>
                                                <li>Hypovolemia (whatever the cause)</li>
                                                <li>Congestive heart failure</li>
                                                <li>Renal failure</li>
                                                <li>Nephrotic syndrome</li>
                                                <li>Lupus nephropathy</li>
                                                <li>Severe hepatic dysfunction (serum albumin &lt;25 g/l or Child-Pugh
                                                    score 10)'</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
