                                        <div class="card-body">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>
                                                    Ketamine is contraindicated in patients in whom a significant
                                                    elevation of blood pressure
                                                    would constitute a serious hazard, such as those patients with
                                                    hypertension, stroke, head
                                                    trauma or intracranial mass, or intracranial bleeding. Similarly,
                                                    ketamine should be used
                                                    with caution in patients with increased intracranial pressure or
                                                    increased intraocular
                                                    pressure (e.g., glaucoma) because these pressures may increase
                                                    significantly after a
                                                    single dose of ketamine.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                    Use ketamine with caution in patients with a history of
                                                    thyrotoxicosis because they are at
                                                    an increased risk of developing tachycardia and hypertension due to
                                                    ketamine-induced
                                                    cardiac stimulation.
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>

